The area covers the old province of Dauphiné, once known as the "larder" of France,[dubious  – discuss] that gave its name to gratin dauphinois,[12] traditionally made in a large baking dish rubbed with garlic. Successive layers of potatoes, salt, pepper and milk are piled up to the top of the dish. It  is then baked in the oven at low temperature for 2 hours.[13]
